<article id="post-1005" class="post-1005 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-costa-rica category-general category-travel tag-airlines tag-cats tag-immigration tag-pets">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/how-to-bring-a-pet-into-costa-rica-simplified/" rel="bookmark">How to bring a pet into Costa Rica: Simplified</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Okay, so a while back I was having kittens (pun intended) about bringing Asia into Costa Rica. Mostly because I simply could not seem to get a straight answer from anyone about the proper process. <a href="http://www.sowrey.org/2008/06/bringing-my-cat-into-costa-rica/">It was driving me batty.</a><br />
So, to anyone bringing in their (small) dog or cat (this might also work for rabbits, but don&#8217;t expect success with gerbils or hamsters or any form of rodent; and it&#8217;s a one-way trip for all birds, you can&#8217;t take them out again) into Costa Rica, allow me to present the (current) process. It&#8217;s really easy.<br />
 <a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/how-to-bring-a-pet-into-costa-rica-simplified/#more-1005" class="more-link">Continue reading<span class="screen-reader-text"> &#8220;How to bring a pet into Costa Rica: Simplified&#8221;</span></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=49&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r' srcset='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/095609f98b14811f33ecac14add504b3?s=98&#038;d=mm&#038;r=r 2x' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49' loading='lazy'/><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="http://geoff.wp/author/sonworf/">Geoff</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/how-to-bring-a-pet-into-costa-rica-simplified/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2008-06-16T11:36:00-06:00">16 June 2008</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/category/costa-rica/" rel="category tag">Costa Rica</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/general/" rel="category tag">General</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/category/travel/" rel="category tag">Travel</a></span><span class="tags-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Tags </span><a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/airlines/" rel="tag">airlines</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/cats/" rel="tag">cats</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/immigration/" rel="tag">immigration</a>, <a href="http://geoff.wp/tag/pets/" rel="tag">pets</a></span><span class="comments-link"><a href="http://geoff.wp/2008/06/how-to-bring-a-pet-into-costa-rica-simplified/#comments">21 Comments<span class="screen-reader-text"> on How to bring a pet into Costa Rica: Simplified</span></a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
